      "code": "BUFN670",
      "name": "Financial Mathematics",
      "credits": {
        "Amount": 2
      },
      "gen_eds": null,
      "description": "Introduction to the mathematical models used in finance and economics with emphasis on pricing derivative instruments. Topics include elements from basic probability theory, distributions of stock returns, elementary stochastic calculus, Ito's Lemma, arbitrage pricing theory, and continuous time portfolio theory. Particular focus is on the financial applications of these mathematical concepts.",
