    {
      "code": "BUFN710",
      "name": "Financial Strategy for Corporations",
      "credits": {
        "Amount": 2
      },
      "gen_eds": null,
      "description": "An advanced course in corporate finance, focusing on the issues that firms face when they plan to raise external capital from financial markets. The focus is on the financing problems faced by mid-market to large firms and on capital raised from public markets. The forms of external finance vary from simple debt or equity to more complex securities that bundle with an element of risk management.",
