    {
      "code": "BUFN712",
      "name": "Financial Restructuring",
      "credits": {
        "Amount": 2
      },
      "gen_eds": null,
      "description": "Focuses on identifying ways to increase firm value through corporate restructuring. Specific topics include: mergers and tender offers, spin-offs, carve-outs, divestitures, takeover defense strategies, leveraged buy-outs, and international acquisitions. Additionally, the theory, practice and empirical evidence related to each of these topics will be covered. Emphasis will be placed on valuation analysis and strategic considerations.",
